There will always be some hindu rite or ritual or purana or traditions which cannot be defended with sciences and logic, etc.  Let us drop the necessity to reason out our traditiion and practices.  There is no such need.  The day we as a community learn to proudly practice our traditions and devotional and spiritual practices, saying "These are not matters of logic.  We do like this only". That is the day Bharat and Sanatan Dharma and Hindus can walk fearlessly on this land.  Till such time we will keep running and hiding.  Time for pride in what our parents, grand parents and forefathers did.   If this message sounds good to you, then adopt it and echo it everywhere.
